data.name: Cheeseburger Sliders
data.quickTastyDescription: Mini cheeseburgers packed with flavor, perfect for a quick bite or a party!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix the ground beef with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder.
Form the beef into small patties, about 2-3 inches wide.
Cook the patties on a skillet over medium heat for about 3-4 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked.
Place a slice of cheddar cheese on each patty during the last minute of cooking to melt.
While the patties are cooking, slice the slider buns in half and lightly toast them in the oven for 5 minutes.
Assemble the sliders by placing each patty on a bottom bun, adding ketchup, mustard, pickles, and onions as desired, then top with the other half of the bun.
